response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Fizz Buzz Counter\", \"description\": \"Write a function `fizz_buzz` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns the number of Fizz, Buzz, and FizzBuzz values in the range from 1 to `n`. For more information on how Fizz Buzz works, see [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fizz_buzz).\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef fizz_buzz(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the number of Fizz, Buzz, and FizzBuzz values in the range from 1 to `n`.\", \"code\": \"def fizz_buzz(n: int) -> int:\\n    count = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 == 0:\\n            count += 1\\n        elif i % 3 == 0:\\n            count += 0.5\\n        elif i % 5 == 0:\\n            count += 0.5\\n        else:\\n            count += 1\\n    return int(count)\", \"tests\": [\"assert fizz_buzz(15) == 25\", \"assert fizz_buzz(20) == 32\", \"assert fizz_buzz(30) == 43\", \"assert fizz_buzz(1) == 1\"] }"
